<Content>Incredible hotel, absolutely superb customer service Short answer: Incredible hotel, absolutely superb customer service, one of the best I have every stayed at anywhere in the world.We stayed there in April 2007, two adults and a 10 year old child. For our Italy trip, with stops in various cities, I priced hotels through various means, including consolidators like Expedia and Travelocity, certain smaller booking websites, and correspondence with the hotels directly (either by e-mail or telephone). In this particular case I found the best deal at the Grand Hotel Florence by booking through the Five Star Alliance Hotels.I had also e-mailed the hotel that this was a special trip for my 10 year old daughter鈥檚 birthday, and requested that they assign us a nice room. When we arrived, before we had even finished registering, then entire front desk and concierge staff popped up to wish my daughter a happy birthday. For my daughter鈥檚 birthday, the hotel had upgraded us to a magnificent room at no extra charge --- a huge room, with two sets of French doors and twin balconies overlooking the Arno River, canopied bed, gilded mirrors, chandeliers, ornately painted and decorated coffered ceiling, gigantic bathroom. There were a few gifts from the hotel waiting for my daughter in the room. When we came down later for lunch, they presented her with a marbleized travel journal, and the next day gave her a chocolate Easter egg the size of an American football (much to the chagrin of my health-conscious wife!). Our room also contained, in addition to the standard sets of bathrobes and slippers, a child-sized bathrobe and slippers! I have never seen that at any other hotel, anywhere.Interestingly enough, when we went to the Galleria dell'Accademia to see Michelangelo鈥檚 鈥淒avid,鈥?I met an American executive from the Starwood hotel group, which owns the Grand Hotel Florence. He told me that Starwood was aggressively enhancing their customer relations and options for families and children, largely in response to the many customers who said, in effect, 鈥淚 don鈥檛 care about me, just treat my kid right.鈥?br/>When we arrived in our rental car, I asked the doorman to park it for me in the nearest garage, about 2 blocks away. He advised me that if I parked it myself I could save the additional $30 per day that the hotel would have to charge me in VAT. I much appreciated that tip.The restaurant is small, but the food is excellent. Room service was superb. Very good exercise room, as well.The desk clerk always called us by name and went out of his way to ask to help. Many hotels treat customers like honored guests. The Grand Hotel Florence treated us like old and valued friends of the family. 
